Summary

 Dragon3D is a Java framework for the Renderman (c) Interface to convert the Renderman (c) Interface Bytestream (RIB) file format into XML.
 By transforming the RIB into XML devlopers will be able to manupilate the Renderman files with a wide variete of existing XML tools.
 A possible implementation could be the conversion of a Renderman file to another 3D format via XSLT.